# Security Baseline

## RLS

- Every table has RLS enabled. No exceptions.
- Policies are explicit. Fail closed.
- `auth.uid()` is null for anon → policies handle this case.

## Secrets

- NEVER commit. `.env` in `.gitignore`.
- App config via `--dart-define` or `flutter_dotenv` (loaded at startup, never in source).
- Supabase anon key only in client. Service role key is server-only (Edge Functions, admin tooling).

## Input validation

- Server-side validation in Postgres functions and CHECK constraints.
- Client validation is UX, not security.
- Sanitize before storage even when type-safe (e.g., trim, length cap on free text).

## PII

- No PII in logs (names, emails, locations).
- Log user IDs (UUID) instead.
- Crash reporting: scrub PII before send.

## Auth

- Auth state via `supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange`, NOT a bool in shared prefs.
- Sensitive ops (delete account, change email) require recent reauth.
- Apple Sign-In: respect "Hide my email" relay.

## Dependencies

- `flutter pub outdated` weekly.
- Pin major versions in `pubspec.yaml`.
- Audit transitive deps after any new package.

## Reporting

- If a vulnerability is reported, log it as a bug-NNNN with severity P0 and follow the incident-response runbook (engineering-incident-response when written).


